\begin_inset Formula $\pi_{1}:R_{1}\times R_{2}\to R_{1}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi_{2}:R_{1}\times R_{2}\to R_{2}$
\end_inset

 be the projection maps, i.e.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi_{1}(a,b)=a$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi_{2}(a,b)=a$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $(a,b)\in R_{1}\times R_{2}$
\end_inset

.
 In fact, these are more than just maps, they are ring homomorphisms: For
 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi_{1}$
\end_inset

, we have
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\pi_{1}((a,b)(c,d)) & =\pi_{1}(ac,bd)\\
 & =ac\\
 & =\pi_{1}(a,d)\pi_{1}(c,d)
\end{align*}

