\begin_inset Formula $I=I_{1}\times I_{2}$
\end_inset

.
 Suppose 
\begin_inset Formula $(x,y)\in I$
\end_inset

.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi_{1}(x,y)=x$
\end_inset

 tells us that 
\begin_inset Formula $x\in I_{1}$
\end_inset

.
 Similarly, 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi_{2}(x,y)=y$
\end_inset

