\begin_inset Formula $x\in I_{1}=\pi_{1}(I)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $y\in I_{2}=\pi_{2}(I)$
\end_inset

 implies 
\begin_inset Formula $(x,y)\in I$
\end_inset

.
 So 
\begin_inset Formula $I\supset I_{1}\times I_{2}$
\end_inset

.
 Therefore 
\begin_inset Formula $I=I_{1}\times I_{2}$
\end_inset

